      "description": "The Care Act regulations and guidance for local authorities have been strengthened as a result of consultation.  ",
      "document_type": "news_story",
      "first_published_at": "2014-10-23T14:52:14+01:00",
      "locale": "en",
      "public_updated_at": "2014-10-23T14:52:14+01:00",
      "publishing_app": "whitehall",
      "rendering_app": "frontend",
      "schema_name": "news_article",
      "title": "Final Care Act guidance published",
      "updated_at": "2025-03-24T13:57:11+00:00",
      "details": {
        "body": "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/updating-our-care-and-support-system-draft-regulations-and-guidance\" class=\"govuk-link\">government response</a> explains how the regulations and guidance, which come into effect from April 2015, have been revised as a result of the suggestions we received during the consultation.</p>\n\n<p>We have made changes that include clarifying the guidance on adult safeguarding and revising the eligibility criteria to focus on outcomes and better address social isolation.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/updating-our-care-and-support-system-draft-regulations-and-guidance\" class=\"govuk-link\">revised regulations</a> and <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/care-act-2014-statutory-guidance-for-implementation\" class=\"govuk-link\">guidance for local authorities</a> there will be more materials to help those implementing the Care Act on <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.local.gov.uk/care-support-reform\" class=\"govuk-link\">the Local Government Association’s website.</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/care-act-2014-part-1-factsheets\" class=\"govuk-link\">Care Act factsheets</a> have also been updated.</p>\n\n<p>The Care Act aims to make the social care system fairer and help people get better care.</p>\n</div>",
